y Design includes a dialogue between Hise, Deverell, and widely admired landscape architect Laurie Olin that illuminates the significance of the Olmsted-Bartholomew report and situates it in the history of American landscape planning.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aArchitecture. 4aGeneral. 4aHistory. 7aARCHITECTURE / History / General.2bisacsh1 aDeverell, William F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHise, Greg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOlin, Laurie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022415540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092519940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520925199423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520925199/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles